	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You could try running SMS and GBC games in &quot;slivervision&quot;. It's not perfect, but it's at least better than &quot;GBC ONLY&quot; error messages.<br /><ul><li>Set a constant palette 0F001020 0F172720 0F112120 plus a fourth possibly used for the UI. </li><li>Output GBC games' graphics in 4-level grayscale, possibly with some sort of Bayer dithering. </li><li>For each 8x1 pixel sliver, calculate the sliver's average chroma, test whether it's closer to gray, orange, or teal, and output that as the attribute. You can do this by calculating I from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YIQ" class="postlink">YIQ</a> or Co from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YCgCo" class="postlink">YCgCo</a>. Co in particular is just R - B. </li></ul>Put in slivervision for SMS and GBC, and I just might buy one.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


