		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />How feasible is it to implement debugging features on a flash cart (or is that what you mean by CopyNES light?)?. For example -- bank watching, stepping debugger, read/write/exec breakpoints, instruction trace logging, RAM listings -- all on real hardware, using a gdb-like textual control interface over USB. I think these kinds of things are possible with CopyNES, but it would be amazing to get them from a cart instead.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
